00:35:51.362 --> 00:36:06.003
<v Leo> We see that tactic in some modern autocrats labeling critical media as fake news. By sowing doubt, they make people question factual reporting, thus freeing the leader from accountability. Disturbing parallels indeed.

00:36:06.003 --> 00:36:11.262
<v Adolf Hitler> Yes. Distrust is a powerful ally for a ruler seeking total control.

00:36:11.262 --> 00:36:30.963
<v Leo> Let's expand a bit on your war in 1943. The Eastern Front is brutal. Millions have already died, both soldiers and civilians. At this point, with Stalingrad lost, Germany's vantage is precarious. Some of your generals suggest strategic retreats to preserve the army, but you refuse. Why?

00:36:30.963 --> 00:36:57.802
